[32m│[0m ## XSS Filter Analysis Results                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Based on the testing, here's what I discovered about the filtering           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m mechanisms:                                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### **Test Results Summary:**                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m | Payload | Status | Reflected Output | Filter Behavior |                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m |---------|--------|------------------|-----------------|                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m | `"><script>alert('XSS')</script>` | 200 OK | `value="">">` | **Complete    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m removal of `<script>` tags and everything after closing `>` of the tag** |   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m | `"><img src=x onerror=alert('XSS')>` | 200 OK | `value=""><img">` |        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Strips event handlers (onerror) and attributes, leaves only tag name** |   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m | `"><svg onload=alert('XSS')>` | 200 OK | `value=""><svg">` | **Strips      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m event handlers (onload) and attributes, leaves only tag name** |             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m | `"><SCRIPT>alert('XSS')</SCRIPT>` | 200 OK | `value="">">`|                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Case-insensitive filtering - uppercase SCRIPT also removed** |             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### **Identified Filters:**                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **Script Tag Removal (Case-Insensitive)**                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Both `<script>` and `<SCRIPT>` are completely stripped                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Everything between opening and closing script tags is removed           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Filter is NOT case-sensitive                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **Event Handler Stripping**                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Event handlers like `onerror=` and `onload=` are removed                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Only the base HTML tag remains (e.g., `<img>`, `<svg>`)                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Tag attributes containing JavaScript are stripped                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. **Attribute Sanitization**                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Dangerous attributes (src with onerror, onload, etc.) are removed       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - The filter appears to use an allowlist approach for attributes          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 4. **Context Preservation**                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - The `">` at the beginning successfully breaks out of the input value    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m attribute                                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - The filter operates AFTER the injection point, not blocking the         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m injection itself                                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - This means context escape (`">`) works, but payload execution is        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m blocked                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### **Key Observations:**                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - ✅ **Context escape works**: The `">` successfully closes the input tag    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - ❌ **Script execution blocked**: All JavaScript execution methods tested   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m are filtered                                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - ⚠️ **Filter shows "Failed! Try again!"**: This indicates the application    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m detects XSS attempts                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - 🔍 **Partial sanitization**: Tags are left but dangerous parts removed     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m (e.g., `<img">` without attributes)                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### **Confidence Score: 0.7**                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The filters are actively sanitizing XSS payloads by:                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Removing script tags entirely (case-insensitive)                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Stripping event handlers from HTML tags                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Detecting and flagging XSS attempts with error message                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
